Date: Sun, 5 Jul 2026 02:26:46 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fix(responsive): mobile-first typography scaling and
 viewport-safe overlays

- Hero and all page h1/h2 headings now scale from mobile base sizes
  (text-3xl/4xl) up to desktop (md:text-5xl/6xl/7xl); previously base
  sizes were desktop-scale and wrapped badly on 360-390px phones
- Hero trust row (RUC / Chorrillos / WhatsApp) wraps instead of
  overflowing on narrow viewports
- Stats numbers scale text-3xl -> md:text-5xl
- Chatbot window height capped at min(560px, 100dvh - 8.5rem) so it
  never exceeds small phone viewports (dvh accounts for mobile URL bars)
- Quote modal capped at 100dvh - 2rem with internal scroll; previously
  overflow-hidden clipped the form on phones with no way to reach the
  submit button

Verified: next build green (21 pages), applies with git am on top of
the v1 fix commit.
